---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy – QuitDr"
  description="QuitDr's Privacy Policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal and health information in compliance with Australian privacy laws."
>
  <section class="page-hero" style="padding:3rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>How we collect, use, store, and protect your information.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:2rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <span class="legal-last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</span>

        <p>QuitDr ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy and handling your personal and health information in accordance with the <strong>Privacy Act 1988 (Cth)</strong> and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).</p>

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>QuitDr is an Australian telehealth service providing doctor-led smoking cessation support. We connect patients with Australian-registered doctors for telehealth consultations and facilitate medication delivery through partner pharmacies.</p>

        <h2>2. What Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect the following categories of personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Identity information:</strong> Full name, date of birth, state/territory.</li>
          <li><strong>Contact information:</strong> Email address, phone number, delivery address.</li>
          <li><strong>Health information (sensitive):</strong> Smoking history, medical conditions, current medications, allergies, pregnancy status, and other information provided in your intake form.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment information:</strong> Processed securely via Stripe. We do not store your card details.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical information:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited, and usage data collected via cookies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Collect Information</h2>
        <p>We collect information directly from you when you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete the online booking and intake form</li>
          <li>Participate in a telehealth consultation</li>
          <li>Make a payment through our platform</li>
          <li>Contact our support team</li>
          <li>Use our website (cookies and analytics)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal and health information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide telehealth medical consultations</li>
          <li>Facilitate prescription issuance and medication delivery</li>
          <li>Communicate appointment details and follow-ups</li>
          <li>Process payments</li>
          <li>Improve our services and platform</li>
          <li>Comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We will not use your health information for marketing purposes without your explicit consent.</p>

        <h2>5. Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
        <p>We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Treating doctors:</strong> Australian-registered doctors providing your telehealth consultation.</li>
          <li><strong>Partner pharmacy:</strong> To fulfil prescriptions and arrange delivery.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment processor:</strong> Stripe (for secure payment processing).</li>
          <li><strong>Technology providers:</strong> Hosting and platform infrastructure providers bound by confidentiality.</li>
          <li><strong>Regulators:</strong> Where required by law, including AHPRA and TGA.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. We do not share individual employee health data with employers — employer reporting is aggregate only.</p>

        <h2>6. Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>Your information is stored on secure, Australian-based servers. We use industry-standard encryption and access controls to protect your data. Health information is treated as sensitive data and subject to additional safeguards.</p>
        <p>We retain health records in accordance with applicable medical record retention obligations under Australian law.</p>

        <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
        <p>Our website uses cookies to improve functionality and user experience. You may disable cookies in your browser settings, but some features of the platform may not function correctly.</p>

        <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under Australian privacy law, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access your personal information held by us</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
          <li>Make a complaint about how we handle your information</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@quitdr.com.au">privacy@quitdr.com.au</a>.</p>

        <h2>9. Complaints</h2>
        <p>If you are unsatisfied with our response to a privacy concern, you may lodge a complaint with the <strong>Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)</strong> at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.</p>

        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The current version is always available on this page with the date of last update.</p>

        <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For privacy-related enquiries: <a href="mailto:privacy@quitdr.com.au">privacy@quitdr.com.au</a></p>

        <div class="compliance-box" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
          <span class="icon">&#128274;</span>
          <span>This service complies with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles. Health information is sensitive information and is subject to additional protections under Australian law.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
